                        "AcquisitionStrategy": {
                            "val": "Competitive contract was awarded in November 2012 and began performance in January 2013.  The CCS-C Production and Sustainment Contract (CPASC) includes effort to increase the capability of the CCS-C system to provide ongoing C2, launch readiness support, and anomaly resolution for MILSATCOM satellite families.  The CCS-C project 657102 funds system architecture evolution to provide increased performance for additional satellites and to comply with DoD, Air Force, and AFSPC-directed standards for Information Assurance, Satellite Control Standardization, and Net-Readiness."
                        }
